        "question_HMLwLd": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What are the conditions of the item?",
            "text": "<p>All our items are carefully refurbished, thoroughly tested, and professionally cleaned to ensure they perform like new. Each product goes through a strict quality check before being shipped to ensure you're getting the best retro gaming experience.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_iYHBR6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Are the games authentic or third-party?",
            "text": "<p>While most of our products are pre-owned and authentic without any third-party or knock-offs, we thoroughly test and refurbish each game and console to ensure they function like new. Quality is our top priority, and we only offer items that meet our strict standards.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_KF7qCj": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the difference between a PS3 fat console and a compatible PS?",
            "text": "<p>The PS3 fat console is the original, bulky version of the PlayStation 3, while a compatible PS (like the PS3 Slim or Super Slim) offers the same gaming experience but with a more compact design and certain updated features, such as improved energy efficiency.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_kaJN7H": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What does “Complete in Box” mean?",
            "text": "<p>\"Complete in Box\" (CIB) means the game includes the original manual, box, and game cartridge or disc, providing collectors with the full packaging as it was originally sold.</p>"
          }
        },
